ARIMA+EGARCH Dynamic Predict Bitcoin Rate of Return

Download data from quandl

Rawdata <- Quandl("BITSTAMP/USD")
LastPrice <- Rawdata$Last[length(Rawdata$Last):1]
OverView=xts(LastPrice,order.by=as.Date(Rawdata$Date[length(Rawdata$Last):1]))
ReturnRate <- dailyReturn(OverView,type="log")
chartSeries(OverView, theme = 'white')

Graphical analysis

From the QQ Plot, we could know that the log return is not a normal distribtion. From the histogram, we could see that spillover and inverse leverage effect.

par(mfcol=c(1,3)) 
hist(ReturnRate,prob = TRUE)
lines(density(ReturnRate))
qqnorm(ReturnRate); qqline(ReturnRate, col = 2)
plot(ReturnRate)

Test distribtion

The kurtosis is 5.9, which obvious larger than 3. The distribution have heavy tails. The p-value of Jarque Bera test is less than 1%, reject H0, the distribution is not a normal distribution. SO, we should use sted for eGARCH.

Test serial correlations

The p-value of Augmented Dickey-Fuller test is 0.01, thus we could reject the null hypothesis that it is a stationary series.

ARCH effects Test

From acf and pacf of ReturnRate^2, we could see the heteroscedasticity. And the p-value of Box-Ljung test is less than 0.01, serial has memory effect, after ARCH heteroscedasticity test for residuals, the p-value is less than 0.01, the residuals has ARCH effects.

Find small AIC of ARMA model

final.aic <- Inf
final.order <- c(0,0,0)
for (p in 0:5) for (q in 0:5){
  if ( p == 0 && q == 0){
    next
  }
  current.aic <- AIC(arima(ReturnRate,order=c(p,0,q)))
  if( current.aic < final.aic){
    final.aic <- current.aic
    final.order <- c(p, 0, q)
    final.arima <- arima(ReturnRate, order=final.order)
  } else {
    next
  }
}
final.order
## [1] 5 0 5

Find suitable eGARCH model

GARCH Model: eGARCH(1,1)

Mean Model: ARIMA(2,0,5)

Distribution: sged

attspec = ugarchspec(
  variance.model=list(model="eGARCH",garchOrder=c(1,1)),
  mean.model=list(armaOrder=c(
    final.order[1], final.order[3]
  ), include.mean=T),
  distribution.model="sged"
)

Dynamic forecast

windowLength = 1400
foreLength = length(ReturnRate) - windowLength
forecasts <- vector(mode="character", length=foreLength)
t1<-Sys.time()
for (d in 0:foreLength) {
  spReturnsOffset = ReturnRate[(1+d):(windowLength+d)]
  final.aic <- Inf
  final.order <- c(0,0,0)
  for (p in 0:5) for (q in 0:5) {
    if ( p == 0 && q == 0) {
      next
    }
    arimaFit = tryCatch( arima(spReturnsOffset, order=c(p, 0, q)),
                         error=function( err ) FALSE,
                         warning=function( err ) FALSE )
    if( !is.logical( arimaFit ) ) {
      current.aic <- AIC(arimaFit)
      if (current.aic < final.aic) {
        final.aic <- current.aic
        final.order <- c(p, 0, q)
        final.arima <- arima(spReturnsOffset, order=final.order)
      }
    } else {
      next
    }
  }

  spec = ugarchspec(
    variance.model=list(model="eGARCH",garchOrder=c(1,1)),
    mean.model=list(armaOrder=c(
      final.order[1], final.order[3]
    ), include.mean=T),
    distribution.model="sged"
  )
  fit = tryCatch(
    ugarchfit(
      spec, spReturnsOffset, solver = "hybrid"
    ), error=function(e) e, warning=function(w) w
  )
  if(is(fit, "warning")) {
    forecasts[d+1] = paste(
      index(spReturnsOffset[windowLength]), 1, sep=","
    )
    print(
      paste(
        index(spReturnsOffset[windowLength]), 1, sep=","
      )
    )
  } else {
    fore = ugarchforecast(fit, n.ahead=1)
    ind = fore@forecast$seriesFor
    forecasts[d+1] = paste(
      colnames(ind), ifelse(ind[1] < 0, -1, 1), sep=","
    )
    print(paste(colnames(ind), ifelse(ind[1] < 0, -1, 1), sep=","))
  }
}
